, although dust-reprocessed radiation pressure and O star\nstellar winds are the most likely candidates. The observed outflows will have a\nvery substantial effect on the clusters' evolution and star formation\nefficiency.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 10 Nov 2020 19:00:00 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 12 Nov 2020 14:59:49 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Sat, 6 Mar 2021 18:58:55 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-05-05"}
