ids grow to pebbles in the\ndisc midplane, this results in a pebble flux of $\\sim\n10-100\\,M_{\\oplus}\\textrm{Myr}^{-1}$ through the inner disc. Our results\ndemonstrate that scattered planetesimals can carry a significant flux of solids\npast planetary-induced gaps in young and massive protoplanetary discs.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 11 Nov 2020 13:37:54 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 8 Mar 2021 11:29:45 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-04-21"}
